<task id="007" project="spaarke-daily-update-service-r4">
  <metadata>
    <title>Deploy BRIEF-VALIDATE-ENTITY-NAMES action row (ActionType 141)</title>
    <phase>1: W0 JPS — Action rows + EntityNameValidator (PR 1)</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>002, 003, 004</dependencies>
    <blocks>011</blocks>
    <tags>jps, dataverse, deploy</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Data deployment via MCP. Depends on the executor (003) + form (004) being in place so the deployed Action row resolves correctly in BFF + PlaybookBuilder palette.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>Follow the `jps-action-create` skill. Author + deploy `sprk_analysisaction` row to spaarkedev1 with `sprk_executoractiontype = 141`, `sprk_actioncode = "BRIEF-VALIDATE-ENTITY-NAMES"`, referencing the EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutor (deployed in task 003). Verify via MCP `read_query` returns the row; verify PlaybookBuilder palette displays the Tool with the new EntityNameValidatorForm (task 004).</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. JPS Action-row author closing the loop on the EntityNameValidator triplet (enum + executor + form + row).</role>

  <goal>One `sprk_analysisaction` row in spaarkedev1 with sprk_executoractiontype = 141, code BRIEF-VALIDATE-ENTITY-NAMES, statecode Active; canonical JSON source committed; PlaybookBuilder palette shows the new Tool wired to the new form.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>R4 FR-3 (lines 116-122) AC-3a (line 119) + AC-3c (line 121) require the deployed Action row to: (a) reference ActionType 141 (deployed via task 002 enum + task 003 executor), (b) appear in the PlaybookBuilder palette wired to the EntityNameValidatorForm (task 004). This task closes the loop on the EntityNameValidator triplet started in tasks 002-004. The DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE playbook (PR 2 task 011) will then reference this Action row by code.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutor.cs</file>
