  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load all knowledge files. Read spec.md FR-3 (lines 116-122) + AC-3a + AC-3c. Confirm tasks 002, 003, 004 complete (TASK-INDEX shows ✅ for each).</step>
    <step order="2">Invoke `jps-action-create` skill to scaffold the BRIEF-VALIDATE-ENTITY-NAMES Action JSON. sprk_executoractiontype = 141; sprk_actioncode = "BRIEF-VALIDATE-ENTITY-NAMES"; sprk_systemprompt with input schema (candidateText + allowList) matching the EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutor contract; sprk_outputschemajson with scrubbedText + removedTerms.</step>
    <step order="3">Author the canonical JSON at `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/actions/brief-validate-entity-names.action.json`.</step>
    <step order="4">Run `jps-validate` against the JSON — fix any errors.</step>
    <step order="5">Check spaarkedev1 for an existing row via `mcp__dataverse__read_query` filtered to sprk_executoractiontype = 141 (idempotency check); upsert via `mcp__dataverse__create_record` or `mcp__dataverse__update_record`.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify via `mcp__dataverse__read_query` SELECT … WHERE sprk_executoractiontype = 141 — returns 1 row, statecode Active.</step>
    <step order="7">Verify PlaybookBuilder palette displays the new Tool (open code page; confirm "Validate Entity Names" or equivalent palette entry visible); clicking the palette entry opens the EntityNameValidatorForm from task 004.</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change this task's status to ✅.</step>
    <step order="9">If deviations from plan, document in projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="mcp-dataverse">read_query / create_record / update_record for sprk_analysisaction upsert</tool>
  </tools>

